<p itemprop="description">Security architecture involves designing and implementing comprehensive security frameworks and controls to protect government systems, data, and infrastructure from security threats and vulnerabilities.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand security architecture principles and recognise the importance of security design in government systems and services.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can contribute to security architecture projects, implement security controls, and apply security patterns and standards in system designs.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design comprehensive security architectures, conduct security assessments, and establish security standards and patterns for government systems.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead enterprise security architecture strategy, establish security governance frameworks, and influence government security policy and standards.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

